.Dd June 11, 2026
.Dt LIBFMOS 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm libfmos.h
.Nd Library to support common Mac OS specific formats
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In libfmos.h
.Pp
Support functions
.nf
.Ft const char *
.Fo libfmos_get_version
.Fa "void"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
Notify functions
.nf
.Ft void
.Fo libfmos_notify_set_verbose
.Fa "int verbose"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_notify_set_stream
.Fa "FILE *stream"
.Fa "libfmos_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_notify_stream_open
.Fa "const char *filename"
.Fa "libfmos_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_notify_stream_close
.Fa "libfmos_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
Error functions
.nf
.Ft void
.Fo libfmos_error_free
.Fa "libfmos_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_error_fprint
.Fa "libfmos_error_t *error"
.Fa "FILE *stream"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_error_sprint
.Fa "libfmos_error_t *error"
.Fa "char *string"
.Fa "size_t size"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_error_backtrace_fprint
.Fa "libfmos_error_t *error"
.Fa "FILE *stream"
.Fc
.fi
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_error_backtrace_sprint
.Fa "libfmos_error_t *error"
.Fa "char *string"
.Fa "size_t size"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
ADC functions
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_adc_decompress
.Fa "const uint8_t *compressed_data"
.Fa "size_t compressed_data_size"
.Fa "uint8_t *uncompressed_data"
.Fa "size_t *uncompressed_data_size"
.Fa "libfmos_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
LZFSE functions
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_lzfse_decompress
.Fa "const uint8_t *compressed_data"
.Fa "size_t compressed_data_size"
.Fa "uint8_t *uncompressed_data"
.Fa "size_t *uncompressed_data_size"
.Fa "libfmos_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.Pp
LZVN functions
.nf
.Ft int
.Fo libfmos_lzvn_decompress
.Fa "const uint8_t *compressed_data"
.Fa "size_t compressed_data_size"
.Fa "uint8_t *uncompressed_data"
.Fa "size_t *uncompressed_data_size"
.Fa "libfmos_error_t **error"
.Fc
.fi
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn libfmos_get_version
function is used to retrieve the library version.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Most of the functions return NULL or \-1 on error, dependent on the return \
type.
For the actual return values see
.In libfmos.h .
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
None
